        "content": "<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<!-- Thie example adapted from the PET Handbook, copyright University of Cambridge ESOL Examinations -->\n<assessmentItem xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1\"\n                xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n                xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1 http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1.xsd\"\n                title=\"\" adaptive=\"false\" timeDependent=\"false\">\n\n<cs:correctResponseFeedback>Correct!</cs:correctResponseFeedback>\n        <cs:incorrectResponseFeedback>Your answer.</cs:incorrectResponseFeedback>\n\n<responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_01\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"identifier\">\n        <correctResponse>\n            <value>ChoiceB</value>\n        </correctResponse>\n    </responseDeclaration>\n    <outcomeDeclaration identifier=\"SCORE\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"integer\">\n        <defaultValue>\n            <value>0</value>\n        </defaultValue>\n    </outcomeDeclaration>\n\n<responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_02\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"identifier\">\n        <correctResponse>\n            <value>ChoiceD</value>\n        </correctResponse>\n    </responseDeclaration>\n    <outcomeDeclaration identifier=\"SCORE\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"integer\">\n        <defaultValue>\n            <value>0</value>\n        </defaultValue>\n    </outcomeDeclaration>\n\n<responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_03\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"identifier\">\n        <correctResponse>\n            <value>ChoiceB</value>\n        </correctResponse>\n    </responseDeclaration>\n    <outcomeDeclaration identifier=\"SCORE\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"integer\">\n        <defaultValue>\n            <value>0</value>\n        </defaultValue>\n    </outcomeDeclaration>\n\n\n    <!-- an Extended text entry response for longer form text entry -->\n    <responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_04\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"string\"/>\n\n   \n\n    <!-- an Extended text entry response for longer form text entry -->\n    <responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_05\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"string\"/>\n\n    <!-- an Extended text entry response for longer form text entry -->\n    <responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_06\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"string\"/>\n\n    <itemBody>\n\n<p class=\"intro-2\">Read the poem and then answer the questions below.</p>\n\n<cs-tabs>\n<cs-tab title=\"Poem\">\n        <resource\n                type=\"passage\"\n                title=\"The Driver\"\n                copyrightOwner=\"Renny Christopher\"\n                />\n\n        <h1 class=\"para-center\" >The Driver</h1>\n       \n       <center class=\"passage-author\">by Renny Christopher</center>\n       \n<div class=\"numbered-lines\">     \n<line>The best time was the mornings</line>\n<line>when the job was far away.</line>\n<line>Dad and I carried our coffee to the truck,</line>\n<line>rode up the crowded highway, quiet,</line>\n<line>Dad driving in his sleep,</line>\n<line>threading traffic in a dream.</line>\n\n<br/>\n\n<line>Once at the job we parked and woke up</line>\n<line>from the freeway dream</line>\n<line>took the tools from the lockbox in the back.</line>\n<line>At lunch we ate in the truckbed</line>\n<line>spare tire and rope coils for our chairs.</line>\n<br/>\n\n<line>On the way home, Dad would talk,</line>\n<line>telling stories of the war he was in</line>\n<line>--the good war he called it--</line>\n<line>or of driving midget race cars</line>\n<line>on tracks all up and down California.</line>\n<line>He told stories of highways he drove</line>\n<line>towing his racecar along--</line>\n<line>the old road over the Cuesta grade,</line>\n<line>the Coast highway to Long Beach</line>\n<line>roads to anywhere that had a dirt track.</line>\n\n<br/>\n\n<line>As he talked he drove one-handed--</line>\n<line>left hand on the wheel, elbow out the window</line>\n<line>in his right hand a bottle of pop</line>\n<line>right foot on the accelerator.</line>\n\n<br/>\n\n<line>Once, he asked me to drive home.</line>\n<line>As I glanced at him in the passenger seat</line>\n<line>I could see in the sunlight through the windshield</line>\n<line>his temples just beginning to go gray.</line>\n\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"note-tip\">Taken from <i>Longing Fervently for Revolution</i> Renny Christopher/Slipstream Press</div><p/>\n\n</cs-tab>\n</cs-tabs>\n\n<hr class=\"element-seperator\"/>\n\n<choiceInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_01\" shuffle=\"false\" maxChoices=\"1\">\n            <prompt>The tone of the poem reveals what about the speaker?</prompt>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceA\">The speaker is angry about the past.\n                 <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_01\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceA\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceB\">The speaker is sentimental about the past.\n                 <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_01\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceB\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceC\">The speaker is proud of the past.\n                 <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_01\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceC\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceD\">The speaker is disgusted by the past.\n                 <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_01\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceD\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n        </choiceInteraction>\n\n\n<choiceInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_02\" shuffle=\"false\" maxChoices=\"1\">\n        <prompt>What literary device is used in lines 5-6?</prompt>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceA\">Simile\n                <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_02\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceA\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceB\">Metaphor\n                <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_02\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceB\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceC\">Personification\n                <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_02\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceC\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceD\">Hyperbole\n                <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_02\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceD\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n        </choiceInteraction>\n        \n        \n<choiceInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_03\" shuffle=\"false\" maxChoices=\"1\">\n            <prompt>In the last line of the poem the speaker uses the phrase “his temples just beginning to go gray” to represent</prompt>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceA\">his fears for his father\n                <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_03\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceA\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceB\">the passage of time\n                <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_03\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceB\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceC\">the highs and lows of the father’s life\n                <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_03\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceC\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceD\">the darkness in his relationship with his father        \n                <feedbackInline\n     outcomeIdentifier=\"Q_03\"\n     identifier=\"ChoiceD\"\n     defaultFeedback=\"true\"></feedbackInline></simpleChoice>\n        </choiceInteraction>\n        \n        \n\n<p class=\"prompt\"><i>Both the speaker and the father enjoy their work days together.</i> Do you agree with this statement? Explain your choice by using specific details from the poem.</p>\n<extendedTextInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_04\" expectedLength=\"200\" class=\"answer_5_linebox\"></extendedTextInteraction>\n\n\n        \n<p class=\"prompt\"><i>The father teaches the speaker that dreaming is better than doing.</i> Do you agree with this statement? Explain your choice by using specific details from the poem.</p>\n    <extendedTextInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_05\" expectedLength=\"200\" class=\"answer_5_linebox\"></extendedTextInteraction>\n\n<p class=\"prompt\">Explain, by using specific details from the poem, how “The Driver” explores the role of memory to characterize relationships.</p>\n    <extendedTextInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_06\" expectedLength=\"200\" class=\"answer_5_linebox\"></extendedTextInteraction>\n    </itemBody>\n</assessmentItem>"
